    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="682" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d682">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Dwight now says all missionaries in the interior will be sacrificed
                            unless united Christian powers intervene to stop massacre. I have no
                            hope of European concert. Mr. Dwight has written missionary boards. Tell
                            them I can get vessels to take their friends to Christian ports. If <pb facs="0664" n="1398" xml:id="pg_1398"/> men wish to remain, I will
                            get escort for all to seacoast, and men can return; but women and
                            children should visit America. Observe, I gave no advice, but state
                            facts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
